The culture of pride in “doing straight” still exists, he said, adding that modern technology and the growing pressure on students makes this a growing problem.
Ensuring that we sleep enough and with quality should be a “secret weapon” for students to combat stress, exhaustion and anxiety, he said, and even to avoid fattening, as sleep deprivation puts the brain in starvation mode, making them constantly starving.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old Californian student of physical biology and chemistry, helped Professor Czeisler design the course after attending one of his classes last year in his first year at Harvard.
