The bat populations in Scotland and across the UK have declined considerably over the last century.
These animals are threatened by construction and development work that affect dormitories and make habitat scarce.
Wind turbines and lightning also pose a threat, along with fly-killing papers and some chemical treatments of building materials, in addition to domestic cat attacks.
In fact, bats are not blind.
